page.title: 03TRANSPORT
page.content: { { Transport } There are no railway lines or through waterways in this area. The major transport route is the A58 Wetherby Rd, which runs north-east to meet the A6120 Leeds Ring Rd. The A58 carries approx. 1000 cars, 150 lorries, 40 buses, 285 vans, 7 motorcycles, 7 taxis, 2 caravans, 2 ambulances and 3 police cars per hour. Other busy roads include the Ring Rd with 780 cars, Princes Avenue 720 cars, Old Park Rd 390 cars and Canal Rd 270 cars per hour. Buses to and from Leeds travel on Princes Ave, Wetherby Rd,Monkswood Avenue and Kentmere Ave. West Yorkshire buses journey between Leeds and Wetherby. There is a Ring Rd service from Horsforth to Seacroft.
